author: BBC News
description: Chelsea Manning will be released after serving seven years in prison. Her lawyer speaks to the BBC about what's next.
title: What next for Chelsea Manning after release?

author: http://xml.zeit.de/autoren/G/Hauke_Gierow/index
description: Es ist ein bisschen Gerechtigkeit für eine große Frau: Chelsea Manning kommt vorzeitig aus der Haft frei. Sie hat weit mehr getan, als nur geheime Dokumente zu leaken.
title: Whistleblowerin: Danke, Chelsea Manning!

author: Spiegel Online
description: Die US-Whistleblowerin Chelsea Manning ist frei. Darüber kann man sich freuen - aber nur kurz. Ihre Freilassung ist eine Ausnahme, die Missstände bestehen fort.
title: Chelsea Manning: Längst kein Happy End

author: Alle Beiträge von dpa  anzeigen.
description: Zu 35 Jahren Haft wurde Chelsea Manning im Jahr 2010 verurteilt – wegen Geheimnisverrat. Jetzt ist die Whistleblowerin wieder auf freiem Fuß. Auch Julian Assange schöpft wieder Hoffnung.
title: Whistleblowerin entlassen: Chelsea Manning ist frei

author: Spiegel Online
description: Chelsea Manning sollte ursprünglich 35 Jahre in Haft, am Ende waren es sieben Jahre. Am Mittwoch hat die Whistleblowerin das Gefängnis in Kansas verlassen.
title: US-Whistleblowerin: Chelsea Manning ist frei

author: Russell Brandom
description: The US Army is confirming that Chelsea Manning has been released from detention at Fort Leavenworth, in accordance with the commutation of her sentence. She had served just short of seven years...
title: Chelsea Manning has been released from prison

author: Ben Kew
description: Chelsea Manning will reportedly receive free health care and remain on active duty after being released from prison.
title: Chelsea Manning to Remain on Active Duty, Receive Free Health Care after Release - Breitbart

author: Jane Onyanga-Omara, and Tom Vanden Brook
description: Pvt. Chelsea Manning was released from prison Wednesday after serving seven-years of a 35-year sentence for leaking thousands of diplomatic cables and other secret documents to WikiLeaks, the BBC reports. The transgender soldier, who entered prison as Bradley Manning, will remain an active-duty, unpaid soldier.
title: Chelsea Manning released from prison, U.S. Army says

author: Lizzie Dearden
description: Chelsea Manning has been released from prison after being convicted of passing classified information to WikiLeaks. Ms Manning served seven years of her 35-year sentence, which was commuted by Barack Obama as one of his final acts as President.
title: Chelsea Manning has just been released from prison
